 BY FOLASHADE KEHINDE Amid controversies surrounding the National Convention of the ruling All Progressives Congress, fixed for February 26, 2022, the party’s Caretaker Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee has officially notified the Independent National Electoral Commission. The notification was given in a letter, addressed to the INEC Chairman, dated February 2 and jointly signed by Governor Mai Mala Buni and the CECPC Secretary, Sen. John Akpanudoedehe. It reads in part: “Follow up to our letter referenced APC/NHDQ/INEC/19/021/40 dated 11th July, 2021 on the Notice for the Conduct of National Convention. “This is to inform the Commission that our great Party has scheduled to hold its National Convention on Saturday, 26th February 2022. “This serves as a formal notification pursuant to the provisions of Section 85 of the Electoral Act (2010) as amended. “Kindly arrange for your officials to monitor the exercise accordingly. “While hoping to receive your cooperation, please accept the assurances of our highest esteem.” 